This paper is about facial landmark localization using a neural network approach, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the architecture of the network and its learning and inference efficiency, which suggests that it may also belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which could place it under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method compared to other state-of-the-art methods, which suggests that it may also belong to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
